## Minito Codebase Detailed Guide

This guide explains how the entire Minito platform works, covering backend architecture, database interaction, frontend flow, all major modules, and the complete user journey for each role. Every file and key logic path is expanded so you can understand the system end-to-end.

---

## 1. Project Overview

Minito is a multi-role “quick-commerce” system built as a real-world logistics-enabled e-commerce platform. It supports:

- **Customers** for browsing, cart, wallet, ordering, and order tracking
- **Admins** for product/user/store/employee management and analytics
- **Store Managers** for inventory, order packing, restock, flash sale, expiration handling
- **Delivery Partners** for claiming available orders, updating delivery status, and tracking earnings

It is built as a **Flask backend** + **React frontend**, with **MySQL** as the database engine.

