### 4.6 Delivery APIs: delivery.py

This module manages delivery partner operations.

#### Assigned orders

- `GET /delivery/orders/<partner_id>`
- returns active assigned orders for partner
- joins customer information
- loads items for each order

#### Available orders

- `GET /delivery/available-orders/<store_id>`
- returns orders in `Packed` state without `DeliveryPartnerID`

#### Claiming orders

- `POST /delivery/accept-order`
  - locks delivery partner row
  - verifies partner is available
  - locks order row
  - ensures no one else claimed it
  - updates order status to `Picked`
  - marks partner unavailable

This is the main safety logic preventing double assignment.

#### Earnings

- `GET /delivery/earnings/<partner_id>`
- computes:
  - completed delivered orders today
  - total commission earned today
  - total wallet balance
  - history of last 10 completed order commissions

#### Order status updates

- `POST /delivery/orders/update`
- if marking `Delivered`, it:
  - locks the order
  - sets `CommissionEarned = 50` if not already set
  - credits delivery partner wallet
  - frees the partner
- otherwise, simply updates order status

